THE ROLE
Expand all
Our client, a leading financial instituion are seeking a Project Manager who is trained in multiple Call Centre areas. The incumbent will be responsible for resolving customer service issues within a set timeframes. This role will be to ensure world class customer service and the support of sales staff.
- Manage strategic projects
- Drive Best Practices
- Oversee complete Scope Management, Risk Planning, Task Management
- Providing SLA and costs for existing solution prior to business case/proposal development
- Conducting process and system studies and coordinating with team members for system design & integration, application maintenance
- Handling various technical aspects such as software design, coding of modules, monitoring critical paths
- Creating test plans, test cases, scripts and procedures as part of software development
REQUIREMENTS
- Solid Technical knowledge of Call centre technologies/Operations
- Call centre system knowledge such as IVRS, monitoring, knowledge management, workforce management, customer relationship management, automatic call distributor applications
- AVAYA knowledge
- 7+ years of experience leading call centre operations (50-100 agents) providing world class customer service
- Degree in Engineering or Computer Application would be an advantage
ABOUT THE COMPANY
The Adecco Group is the world's leading provider of HR solutions. With more than 33,000 FTE employees and a network of 5,600 branches, in over 60 countries and territories around the world, we offer a wide variety of services, connecting close to 750,000 associates with well over 100,000 clients every day.
The services we offer fall into the broad categories of temporary staffing, permanent placement, career transition, talent development and workforce management solutions, as well as outsourcing and consulting.
The Adecco Group is based in Zurich-Glattbrugg, Switzerland and we are a Fortune Global 500 company listed on the SIX Swiss Exchange.
